Drive Case Resolution in Service Catalog with AI (Beta)

With Einstein Copilot as your AI assistant, your customers resolve their questions without navigating the catalog or requiring agent assistance. Through a generative AI-powered conversational experience, Copilot uses an LLM to identify and execute relevant actions to resolve customer contact reasons. In Service Catalog, Copilot uses actions to open catalog item requests for customers or provides them with a URL link to the item in your catalog.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions with Service Cloud, the Customer Service Catalog add-on, and the Einstein for Service add-on. Einstein generative AI is available in Lightning Experience.

You must have the Service Catalog Builder perm set and Use Einstein Copilot for Salesforce User perm set to use this feature.

Service Catalog provides three custom actions and sample catalog items for common support services: Update Phone Number, Update Email, and Get Help. The flow used in the catalog fulfillment of catalog items determines how Copilot resolves the contact reason. All sample items contain autolaunched flows in their fulfillments, which always result in a catalog item request output.

Copilot also resolves contact reasons by providing customers a URL link to the catalog item in your site that they can request. A URL output is associated only with items that contain orchestration or screen flows in their fulfillment.

Enable Einstein generative AI and turn on Einstein Copilot for Salesforce from the Einstein Copilots page, then configure the provided Service Catalog actions and add them to your Copilot.
title: Drive Case Resolution in Service Catalog with AI
